President Joe Biden addressed attendees at the U.S.-Africa Leaders Summit, held at the Walter E. Washington Convention Center in Washington, D.C. He emphasized the importance of Africa's success and prosperity for global progress and highlighted the need for African leadership in addressing global challenges. President Biden announced several initiatives and investments aimed at strengthening trade, infrastructure, innovation, and entrepreneurship between Africa and the United States. These include an MOU with the African Continental Free Trade Area Secretariat, investments in regional transport and infrastructure projects, support for clean energy, agriculture, and water access, and initiatives to promote digital transformation and cybersecurity. The President also highlighted major business deals and investments made during the summit, totaling over $15 billion. President Biden expressed optimism about the future of the U.S.-Africa partnership and the potential for further collaboration.